      `assignments.resource_id` is VARCHAR while `resources.resource_id`
      is INTEGER. Cast both to `::text` in the subquery.
    - asyncpg rejects string date parameters on TIMESTAMP columns
      (documented gotcha in MEMORY.md). Added `_parse_date_param()` in
      the router that converts `YYYY-MM-DD` strings to `datetime.date`
      before binding — returns HTTP 400 on malformed input rather than 500.
